During the performance of Israeli singer Eden Golan at the final of the Song Contest Eurovision in Malmoe, Sweden. After a week of controversy and threats by pro-Palestina activists, his song 'Hurricane' was whistled, as it had already happened in the semifinals. The 'buu' were however sometimes covered by the applause of the fans of the 20-year-old Israeli singer who launched a kiss to the public at the time of leaving the stage. The final evening opened with the Flag parade in which the 25 artists in the race (one in less than 26 planned after the elimination of the artist of the Netherlands) paraded on stage each with their national flag. The rapper Alyona Alyona and singer Jerry Heil, in race for Ukraine with the song 'Teresa &amp; Maria', closed their performance with an appeal: "Unity for the world. Peace and freedom for Ukraine"
The disqualification of the Dutch singer
Joost Klein, the Dutch competitor at the Eurovision, was disqualified after being investigated by the police for intimidation against a woman member of the show's production team. Klein had disappeared from the evidence on the eve of the final and the organizers of the European Broadcasting Union had explained that yesterday he had been prevented from trying because of an "unspecified incident". "The police are investigating intimidation. The crime was committed on Thursday evening in the arena of Malmo", said to AFP police spokesman Pelle Vamstad "The suspect was heard. He's not in detention," Vamstad added. According to the Dutch broadcaster SVT the incident involved a photographer. During the rehearsal, Klein had paraded with the other participants before the performances but had not climbed on stage when it was his turn. His song "Europapa" is dedicated to his parents, dead when he was small. At the end of the semi-final on Thursday, the 26-year-old seemed to have refused to be side by side with Israeli competitor Eden Golan, covering his face with a Dutch flag in several places.
&nbsp;
The organizers stressed that "unlike some media and social speculations, this incident did not involve any other artist or member of the delegation". I therefore regret that in the accident the Israeli competitor <a href="https://www.agi.it/estero/news/2024-05-11/eurovision-fischi-durante-prove-contcurrent-Israeli-26346870/"> Eden Golan</a> . "The police adopted all the measures and questioned the suspect, the plaintiff and the witnesses," said a spokesman "The investigation was completed and the case will pass to the prosecutor within a few weeks" EBU subsequently confirmed that Klein will not participate in the final.&nbsp;
<h2> Pro-Gaza</h2>
The police dispersed the pro-Palestinian demonstrators around the Malmoe Arena, in southern Sweden, where the final is taking place. Around the structure, police officers loaded protesters on the numerous trucks present, a relatively unusual scene in the Scandinavian country. More than a hundred protesters waved flags at the rhythm of the slogan "Palestina libera". Some wore kefiah, sometimes wrapped on the face. The police, who confirmed that they had used tear gas, were trying to repel the protesters to a square where a pro-Palestinian demonstration had been authorized, to which no one participated. The climate activist Greta Thunberg was among them but remained outside.> You and the members of your group sat in a circle surrounded by the police.
