AGI -&nbsp;&nbsp; Prince Harry played volleyball sitting with the Nigerian army veterans, most injured in the war against the country's Islamic insurrection. During a three-day visit to Nigeria to promote his Invictus Games, the Duke of Sussex and his wife Meghan visited a school for a mental health event.
&nbsp;
In an official cafeteria in Abuja, the yellow-dressed Harry team played against a team led by Nigeria's chief defence chief of state, the country's top commander.<br> The 'Team Harry' lost 25-21 against the commander's team, the CDS Team. On the Duke's team was former Nigerian soldier Peacemaker Azuegbulam, who lost a fighting leg in the northeast, and became the first African to win gold at the Invictus Games in Germany last year.
&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
