"It is an honor for Nigeria and Africa to have Prince Harry here," he told AFP before the game. Before Nigeria, Prince Harry was in London on Wednesday to celebrate the tenth anniversary of the games.<br> As with all his travels to the United Kingdom since he moved to the United States in 2020, his visit aroused renewed speculations on reconciliation with his family. But he didn't meet his father, King Charles.
&nbsp;
Harry founded Invictus in 2014. Since then the games have grown, promoting rehabilitation through sport.<br> Yesterday he went without his wife to Kaduna, in the northwest of Nigeria, to visit a military hospital and speak with the wounded troops in combat. Tomorrow the couple will go to Lagos, the economic capital of the country, to attend a basketball game and participate in a fundraiser.
